<TITLE>Claudia Rusca</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF MENTION="1" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="plain" REG08-TYPE="name" ENTITY="0">Claudia Rusca</REFEX></REF>
 (1593– October 6 1676) was an Italian composer, singer, and organist. 
<REF MENTION="2" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">she</REFEX></REF>
 was a nun at the Umiliate monastery of St. Caterina in Brera. 
<REF MENTION="3" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">she</REFEX></REF>
 learned music at home, before 
<REF MENTION="4" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">she</REFEX></REF>
 professed 
<REF MENTION="5" SYNFUNC="subj-det" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="genitive" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">her</REFEX></REF>
 final vows at the convent. 
<REF MENTION="6" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">she</REFEX></REF>
 probably wrote 
<REF MENTION="7" SYNFUNC="subj-det" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="genitive" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">her</REFEX></REF>
 Sacri concerti à 1–5 con salmi e canzoni francesi (Milan, 1630) for use in the monastery and similar female institutions. The only known copy was destroyed in a fire at the Biblioteca Ambrosiana in 1943.
</PARAGRAPH>
